This paper is about natural language inference, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new model that uses self-attention, which is a popular technique in deep learning for natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the model is designed to work with long sentences or documents, which suggests that it may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) applications such as image captioning.
